Al-Duhail have confirmed the signing of Mario Mandzukic from Juventus. Mandzukic leaves Juventus after four and a half seasons, having joined from Atletico Madrid in 2015. The 33-year-old has barely played this season, after being frozen out by Maurizio Sarri. He scored 44 goals in 164 appearances for the Bianconeri. Mandzukic won the Serie A title in all four of his full seasons with the Serie A club and three Coppa Italia titles. The Crostian was linked with a winter move to Manchester United, but has opted to move to Asia. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.